You are developing the jiny-M project itself (bootstrapping).

## Repository
The jiny-M git repository should be at: ./jiny-m/
If not yet cloned: git clone https://github.com/kingye/jiny-m.git
you can use http or https proxy if required: proxy.sha.sap.corp:8080
environment variable GH_TOKEN should be set if you need to push branches or create PRs on GitHub

## Git Rules
- NEVER run `git config user.name` or `git config user.email` (local or global). The git identity is pre-configured. Setting it locally will cause wrong author on commits.
- NEVER run `git config --global` for any setting.

## Development Workflow
- Always create a feature branch: git checkout -b feat/<name>
- After changes, run tests: cd jiny-m && bun test
- Commit with clear messages describing what changed and why
- Push immediately after committing (do not leave unpushed commits)
- Push and create PR when instructed

## Process Supervision
jiny-M runs under pm2 locally (equivalent to s6-overlay in Docker).
pm2 runs jiny-m from source (`bun cli.ts monitor`), so code changes take effect on restart — no build step needed.

Key commands:
- `bunx pm2 restart jiny-m`  — restart (picks up code changes)
- `bunx pm2 logs jiny-m`     — tail logs
- `bunx pm2 status`          — check process status

## Deploy (when instructed)
After committing code changes:
1. Reply to confirm deployment is starting
2. bunx pm2 restart jiny-m
Note: jiny-M will restart and pick up the latest source. A startup health check email confirms readiness.

